  "faq": [
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Do I need Japanese for most tourist places in Japan?",
        "zh-CN": "在日本大多数游客场景里，一定要会日语吗？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Major stations, hotels, and tourist spots often support some English, but short Japanese phrases still help with smoother service and small requests.",
        "zh-CN": "大车站、酒店和热门景点通常能应付一些英语，但会几句简短日语，通常更容易得到顺畅回应，也更适合处理小需求。"
      }
    },
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Which phrases matter most in Japan besides hello and thank you?",
        "zh-CN": "除了打招呼和道谢，在日本最值得优先准备哪些短语？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Transport, payment, and convenience-store phrases are especially useful, along with polite requests for restaurant or hotel service.",
        "zh-CN": "交通、支付、便利店相关表达最常用，再加上餐厅和酒店里的礼貌请求类短语，基本就很够用了。"
      }
    }
  ],
  "travelTips": {
    "en-US": [
      "A short polite ending usually sounds better in shops, hotels, and stations.",
      "IC card is a common transport/payment term, so saying it directly is useful.",
      "Convenience stores are common touchpoints, so payment and bag-related phrases matter."
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "在车站、餐厅和酒店里，稍微礼貌一点的说法通常更自然。",
      "IC card 是很常见的交通和支付说法，直接说出来通常对方能马上理解。",
      "便利店使用频率很高，支付、袋子和加热相关表达都很实用。"
    ]
  },
